PRELIMINARIES

Loading the data sets (previously saved)

datasets_list <- c("0a", "0b", 1:5)
for( i in datasets_list ) {
    dd <- readRDS(paste0("./data/data", i, "_packed.RDS"))
    assign(paste0("data", i, ".train"), dd$train)
    assign(paste0("data", i, ".test"), dd$test)
    rm(dd)
}

Prediction on Test set

Setting a threshold on the response at 0.2

GLM0a.test.predict <- predict(GLM0a.model, type = "response", newdata = GLM0a.test)

GLM0a.test.performance <- prepare_cmat_performance(predicted = GLM0a.test.predict > GLM0a.threshold, truth = GLM0a.test$Call_Flag)
GLM0a.test.cmat <- GLM0a.test.performance$cmatrix
GLM0a.test.accuracy <- GLM0a.test.performance$accuracy

GLM0a.ROCR_pred_test <- prediction(GLM0a.test.predict, GLM0a.test$Call_Flag)
GLM0a.perf <- performance(GLM0a.ROCR_pred_test, "tpr", "fpr")
GLM0a.AUC <- as.numeric(performance(GLM0a.ROCR_pred_test, "auc")@y.values)

GLM0a.test.performance$AUC <- GLM0a.AUC

The Area Under the Curve (AUC) for this model on the test data is 0.8515, which means that our model can differentiate between a randomly selected retained and non-retained user about 85.15% of the times.

# cutoffs <- seq(0.0, 1.0, by = 0.1)
cutoffs <- seq(0.0, 0.5, by = 0.05)
t.adj <- c(-0.2, 1.7)
str_title <- paste0("ROC Curve : GLM0a")
plot(GLM0a.perf, main = str_title, lwd = 3, colorize = TRUE, print.cutoffs.at = cutoffs, text.adj = t.adj)

flag_ext <- TRUE

# perf_vs_threshold <- list()
perf_vs_threshold <- list(AUC = GLM0a.AUC)
i <- 1
for( threshold in seq(0.05, 0.4, by = 0.05)) {
    i <- i + 1
    this_model <- GLM0a.model
    this_test_data <- GLM0a.test
    this_test_predict <- predict(this_model, type = "response", newdata = this_test_data)
    
    perf_vs_threshold[[i]] <- prepare_cmat_performance(predicted = this_test_predict, 
                                                       threshold = threshold, 
                                                       truth = this_test_data$Call_Flag)
    names(perf_vs_threshold)[i] <- paste0("thr_", sprintf("%4.2f", threshold))
    if( i == 2 ) {
        perf_vs_threshold.table <- print_cmat_performance(perf_vs_threshold[[i]], errors = FALSE, extended = flag_ext, direction = "h")
    } else {
        perf_vs_threshold.table <- rbind(perf_vs_threshold.table, 
                                         print_cmat_performance(perf_vs_threshold[[i]], errors = FALSE, extended = flag_ext, direction = "h"))
    }
    perf_vs_threshold[[i]]$AUC <- GLM0a.AUC
}
GLM0a.perf_vs_threshold <- perf_vs_threshold
GLM0a.perf_vs_threshold$table <- perf_vs_threshold.table
GLM0a.perf_vs_threshold$table$Threshold <- sprintf("**%.2f**", GLM0a.perf_vs_threshold$table$Threshold)
kable(GLM0a.perf_vs_threshold$table, digits = 3, align = "c", caption = "GLM0a Performance Measures vs. Threshold for Classification")

    i <- i + 1
    this_model <- GLM4.model
    this_test_data <- GLM4.test
    this_test_predict <- predict(this_model, type = "response", newdata = this_test_data)
    
    perf_vs_threshold[[i]] <- prepare_cmat_performance(predicted = this_test_predict, 
                                                       threshold = threshold, 
                                                       truth = this_test_data$Call_Flag)
    names(perf_vs_threshold)[i] <- paste0("thr_", sprintf("%4.2f", threshold))
    if( i == 2 ) {
        perf_vs_threshold.table <- print_cmat_performance(perf_vs_threshold[[i]], errors = FALSE, extended = flag_ext, direction = "h")
    } else {
        perf_vs_threshold.table <- rbind(perf_vs_threshold.table, 
                                         print_cmat_performance(perf_vs_threshold[[i]], errors = FALSE, extended = flag_ext, direction = "h"))
    }
    perf_vs_threshold[[i]]$AUC <- GLM4.AUC
}
